>[Difficulty]
>
>
>[Thoughts]
>I know I can use the following definition and theorem:
>1)If for a ring R a positieve integer n exists such that n*a=0 for 
>all a in R, then the least such pos. intg. is the characteristic of R
>2)If R is a ring with unity 1, then R has characteristic n>0 if and 
>only if n is the smallest pos. intg. such that n*1=0.

Hi Viky,

Thanks for writing to Dr Math.  Here's a hint:  If 1 is a unit, then
you would normally expect -1 to be a unit.

If you have any questions about this or need more help, please write
back and show me what you have been able to do, and I will try to
offer further suggestions.

